com.camerontec.catalys.util.fast.codec

Interface IDictionary

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    IntKeyDictionary

    public interface IDictionary
    FAST dictionary.

    Used to look up previous values by internal key.

      • getValueReference

        IValue getValueReference(short key)
        Returns the underlying IValue object used for the given key, creating an underlying IValue if necessary.

        If no value has been defined for the given key, an IValue is returned set to undefined (isUndefined() returns true).

        This method is not used for normal value lookups - getValue(short) should be used for that. This method is used so that the underlying dictionary value object associated with a given key can be looked up just once then its value examined as needed. Avoiding lookups each time, can yield a performance gain.

        Parameters:
        key - Associated with returned IValue.
        Returns:
        Underlying IValue object - never returns null.

      • getValue

        IValue getValue(short key)
        Return the value associated with the given key.

        The value object returned for a given key should not change once it has been assigned. However, the contents of that value object may change.

        If no value is defined for the key, returns null. A value returned from this call will never be isUndefined() (because if it is undefined, null will be returned).

        If the value associated with the key is, in fact, none, an IValue will be returned where isNone() is true.

        If key is negative, will always return null.

        Parameters:
        key - Key to be looked up.
        Returns:
        Value associated with key. May be null. Will never be isUndefined().

      • setValue

        void setValue(short key,
              IValue value)
        Sets the value associated with the given key.

        If value is null or isUndefined(), any value associated with the key is removed.

        IMPORTANT: Since values may be reused, the value stored in the dictionary should be a copy of the value passed in to this call.

        If key is negative, no change is made to the dictionary.

        Parameters:
        key - Key associated with value
        value - Value associated with key
